modules.description: This module provides operations for constructing, modifying, and querying ordered maps with keys of type `name` and generic values, including adding, removing, merging, and inspecting entries. It supports ordered traversal, transformation, and filtering of key-value bindings, enabling functional and imperative manipulation of structured data. Use cases include managing symbolic data structures, configuration settings, or any scenario requiring ordered key-based lookups and transformations.

Compares XML trees by identifying structural and content differences through node-by-node analysis. It processes elements, attributes, and text nodes to highlight changes between versions. Used to track modifications in configuration files or document structures.

Computes differences between XML trees using an algorithm based on structured data change management. Provides ordered maps with string keys and generic values, supporting insertion, deletion, merging, and traversal for structured data manipulation. Enables tasks like tracking configuration changes or analyzing semi-structured data evolution. Examples include comparing document versions or extracting modified elements from XML hierarchies.
